Question : Take a sentence as an input, split it on the basis of space and then count the frequency of each word and output it in a map. 
Solution : 
import java.util.*;
import java.util.Scanner;

public class MyClass {
  public static void main(String args[]) {
     Scanner in=new Scanner(System.in);
        String sentence=in.nextLine();
        String[] words=sentence.split(" ");
        System.out.println(Arrays.toString(words));
        Map<String, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        for(String word : words){
            if(map.containsKey(word)){
                map.put(word,map.get(word) + 1);
            }
            else{
                map.put(word,1);
            }
        }
        System.out.println(map);

  }
}

Things I learnt : 
1. String.split(" ") --> split on the basis of spaces ,String.split("\\s+") --> multiple spaces/tabs basis split
2. Map methods : map.containsKey(), map.get(), map.put()   
3. map.get(key) returns the value associated with the key, to get key, we use either keySet() or entrySet().
